Sentencas: An effective photolithographic process was investigated to fabricate Ni/YSZ pattern anodes using a bi-layer lift-off resist method.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ pattern anodes fabrication and their microstructure and electrochemical behavior changes in H2-H2O environments

Sentencas: Suitable undercut size was found critical for successful pattern fabrication.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ pattern anodes fabrication and their microstructure and electrochemical behavior changes in H2-H2O environments

Sentencas: Effects of Ni thickness, temperature and H2O content on Ni pattern microstructure were evaluated.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ pattern anodes fabrication and their microstructure and electrochemical behavior changes in H2-H2O environments

Sentencas: Ni/YSZ pattern anodes with 0.5 mu m thick Ni was tested in dry H-2 at 550 degrees C without significantly changing the TPB line.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ pattern anodes fabrication and their microstructure and electrochemical behavior changes in H2-H2O environments

Sentencas: Ni/YSZ pattern anodes with Ni thickness of 0.8 mu m were tested at 550 degrees C under dry and humidified H-2 (3-50% H2O) conditions without TPB line change.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ pattern anodes fabrication and their microstructure and electrochemical behavior changes in H2-H2O environments

Sentencas: At 700 degrees C, and for 0.8 mu m thick patterns, the TPB length showed pronounced change in H-2 with 10-50% H2O. Significant increase in TPB length due to holes formation was observed at 800 degrees C with 3% and 10% H2O. Ni/YSZ pattern anodes with 1.0 mu m thick Ni was stable in H-2 with 3% H2O in the range 550-800 degrees C, with TPB line only slightly modified.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ pattern anodes fabrication and their microstructure and electrochemical behavior changes in H2-H2O environments

Sentencas: However, distinct change of TPB line and Ni microstructure was observed with 10-70% H2O above 700 degrees C. Stabilization of the polarization resistance depends on temperature.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ pattern anodes fabrication and their microstructure and electrochemical behavior changes in H2-H2O environments

Sentencas: To accelerate stabilization of the cell, pre-treatment of the cell in H-2 with 3% H2O at 750 degrees C or 800 degrees C could be performed.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ pattern anodes fabrication and their microstructure and electrochemical behavior changes in H2-H2O environments
